enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve modifying the enforcedAttributes map, making addEnforcedAttribute a good candidate for setting up the initial state.
getEnforcedAttributes retrieves the enforced attributes for a tag, which can be used to verify the state before and after calling removeEnforcedAttribute.
isSafeAttribute checks if an attribute is safe for a given tag, which can be used to verify that the removed enforced attribute is no longer considered safe.
After removing an enforced attribute, getEnforcedAttributes can be used to verify that the attribute is no longer present in the enforcedAttributes map.
